obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (6656)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title and extent.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00002_194837_1517807319480&sectionId=6656&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00002_194837_1517807319480
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Census Act, 1948.`
  line
  line `^1[(2) It extends to the whole of India ^2* * *].`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1 Subs., ibid, for the sub-section (2).`
  line
  line `2. The words "except the State of Jammu and Kashmir" omitted by Act 22 of 1959, s. 2 (w.e.f 19-5-1959).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (6657)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes `1 Subs. by Act 11 of 1994, s. 2, for section 2.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00002_194837_1517807319480&sectionId=6657&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00002_194837_1517807319480
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `^1[2. Definitions.— In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires, —`
  line
  line `(a) "premises" means any land, building or part of a building and includes a hut, shed or other`
  line `structure or any part thereof;`
  line
  line `(b) "prescribed" means prescribed by rules made under this Act;`
  line
  line `(c) "vehicle" means any vehicle used or capable of being used for the purpose of road transport,`
  line `whether propelled by mechanical power or otherwise.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_a:
  sectionId (6658)
  sectionNo 2A
  orderNo 3
  title `Rule of construction respecting enactments not extending to Jammu and Kashmir.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_a_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_a_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00002_194837_1517807319480&sectionId=6658&sectionno=2A&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00002_194837_1517807319480
obj_root_law_sections_2_a_content:
  string
  line `2A. [Rule of construction respecting enactments not extending to Jammu and Kashmir.] Omitted by`
  line `the Jammu and Kashmir Reorganization (Adaptation of Central Laws) Order, 2020, vide notification No.`
  line `S.O. 1123(E) dated (18-3-2020) and vide Union Territory of Ladakh Reorganisation (Adaptation of`
  line `Central Laws) Order, 2020, notification No. S.O. 3774(E), dated (23-10-2020).`
obj_root_law_sections_2_a_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (6659)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 4
  title `Central Government to take census.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00002_194837_1517807319480&sectionId=6659&sectionno=3&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00002_194837_1517807319480
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, declare its intention of taking a census in the whole or any part of the territories to which`
  line `this Act extends, whenever it may consider it necessary or desirable so to do, and there upon the census`
  line `shall be taken.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (6660)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 5
  title `Appointment of census staff.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00002_194837_1517807319480&sectionId=6660&sectionno=4&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00002_194837_1517807319480
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may appoint a Census Commissioner`
  line `to supervise the taking of the census throughout the area in which the census is intended to be taken,`
  line `and ^1[Directors of Census Operations] to supervise the taking of the census within the several States.`
  line
  line `(2) The State Government may appoint persons as census-officers ^2[with such designations as that`
  line `Government may deem necessary] to take, or aid in or supervise the taking of, the census within any`
  line `specified local area and such persons, when so appointed, shall be bound to serve accordingly.`
  line
  line `(3) A declaration in writing, signed by any authority authorised by the State Government in this`
  line `behalf, that any person has been duly appointed a census-officer for any local area shall be conclusive`
  line `proof of such appointment.`
  line
  line `(4) The State Government may delegate to such authority as it thinks fit the power of appointing`
  line `census-officers conferred by sub-section (2).`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line `1 . Subs. by Act 56 of 1974, s. 3 and the Second Schedule, for "Superintendents of Census Operations" (w.e.f. 20-12-1974).`
  line
  line `2 Ins. by Act 11 of 1994, s. 3 (w.e.f. 14-1-1994).`
obj_root_law_sections_4_a:
  sectionId (6661)
  sectionNo 4A
  orderNo 6
  title `Staff of every local authority to be made available for taking census.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_a_content
  footnotes `1 Ins. by Act 11 of 1994, s. 4.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00002_194837_1517807319480&sectionId=6661&sectionno=4A&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00002_194837_1517807319480
obj_root_law_sections_4_a_content:
  string
  line `^1 [4A. Staff of every local authority to be made available for taking census.— Every local`
  line `authority in a State shall, when so directed by a written order by the Central Government or by an`
  line `authority appointed by that Government in this behalf, make available to any Director of Census`
  line `Operations such staff as may be necessary for the performance of any duties in connection with the taking`
  line `of census.]`
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (6662)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 7
  title `Status of census authorities as public servants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes `1 Subs by Act 56 of 1974, s. 3 and the Second Schedule for "Superintendents of Census Operations" (w.e.f. 20-12-1974.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00002_194837_1517807319480&sectionId=6662&sectionno=5&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00002_194837_1517807319480
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `The Census Commissioner, all ^1`
  line `[Directors of`
  line `Census Operations] and all census-officers shall be deemed to be public servants within the meaning of`
  line `the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (6663)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 8
  title `Discharge of duties of census-officers in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00002_194837_1517807319480&sectionId=6663&sectionno=6&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00002_194837_1517807319480
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `(1) Where the District Magistrate, or`
  line `such authority as the State Government may appoint in this behalf, by a written order so directs—`
  line
  line `(a) every officer in command of any body of men belonging to the naval, military or air forces, or`
  line `of any vessel of war, of India,`
  line
  line `(b) every person (except a pilot or harbour master) having charge or control of a vessel,`
  line
  line `(c) every person in charge of a lunatic asylum, hospital, workhouse, prison, reformatory or lockup`
  line `or of any public, charitable, religious or educational institution,`
  line
  line `(d) every keeper, secretary or manager of any sarai, hotel, boarding-house, lodging-house,`
  line `immigration depot or club,`
  line
  line `(e) every manager or officer of a railway or any commercial or industrial establishment, and`
  line
  line `(f) every occupant of immovable property wherein at the time of the taking of the census persons`
  line `are living`
  line `shall perform such of the duties of a census-officer in relation to the persons who at the time of the taking`
  line `of the census are under his command or charge, or are inmates of his house, or are present on or in such`
  line `immovable property or are employed under him as may be specified in the order.`
  line
  line `(2) All the provisions of this Act relating to census-officers shall apply, so far as may be, to all`
  line `persons while performing such duties under this section, and any person refusing or neglecting to perform`
  line `any duty which under this section he is directed to perform shall be deemed to have committed an offence`
  line `under section 187 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (6664)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 9
  title `Power to call upon certain persons to give assistance.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00002_194837_1517807319480&sectionId=6664&sectionno=7&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00002_194837_1517807319480
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `The District Magistrate, or such`
  line `authority as the State Government may appoint in this behalf for any local area, may, by written order`
  line `which shall have effect throughout the extent of his district or of such local area, as the case may be, call`
  line upon—
  line
  line `(a) all owners and occupiers of land, tenure-holders, and farmers and assignees of land revenue,`
  line `or their agents,`
  line
  line `(b) all members of the district, municipal, panchayat and other local authorities and officers and`
  line `servants of such authorities, and`
  line
  line `(c) all officers and members of staff of any factory, firm or establishment,`
  line
  line `to give such assistance as shall be specified in the order towards the taking of a census of the persons who`
  line `are, at the time of the taking of the census, on the lands of such owners, occupiers, tenure-holders, farmers`
  line `and assignees, or in the premises of factories, firms and other establishments, or within the areas for`
  line `which such local authorities are established, as the case may be, and the persons to whom an order under`
  line `this section is directed shall be bound to obey it and shall, while acting in pursuance of such order, be`
  line `deemed to be public servants within the meaning of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7_a:
  sectionId (6665)
  sectionNo 7A
  orderNo 10
  title `Requisitioning premises, of vehicles, etc., for taking of a census.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_a_content
  footnotes `1 Ins. by Act 11 of 1994, s. 5 (w.e.f. 14-1-1994).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00002_194837_1517807319480&sectionId=6665&sectionno=7A&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00002_194837_1517807319480
obj_root_law_sections_7_a_content:
  string
  line `^1 [7A. Requisitioning premises, of vehicles, etc., for taking of a census. (1) If it appears to the`
  line `Central Government that, in connection with taking of a census,`
  line
  line `(a) any premises are needed or are likely to be needed, or`
  line
  line `(b) any vehicle, vessel or animal is needed or is likely to be needed,`
  line
  line `that Government may by order in writing requisition such premises, or vehicle, vessel or animal, as the`
  line `case may be, and make such further orders as may appear to it to be necessary or expedient in connection`
  line `with the requisitioning.`
  line
  line `(2) The requisition shall be effected by an order in writing addressed to the person deemed by the`
  line `Central Government to be the owner or person in possession of the property, and such order shall be`
  line `served in the prescribed manner on the person to whom it is addressed.`
  line
  line `(3) Whenever any property is requisitioned under sub-section (1), the period of such requisition shall`
  line `not extend beyond the period for which such property is required for any of the purposes mentioned in`
  line `that sub-section.]`
obj_root_law_sections_7_b:
  sectionId (6666)
  sectionNo 7B
  orderNo 11
  title `Payment of compensation.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 11 of 1994, s. 5 (w.e.f. 14-1-1994).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00002_194837_1517807319480&sectionId=6666&sectionno=7B&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00002_194837_1517807319480
obj_root_law_sections_7_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[7B. Payment of compensation.-- (1) Whenever in pursuance of section 7A the Central Government`
  line `requisitions any premises, there shall be paid to the persons interested compensation the amount of which`
  line `shall be determined by taking into consideration the following, namely:`
  line
  line `(i) The rent payable in respect of the premises or if no rent is so payable, the rent payable for`
  line `similar premises in the locality;`
  line
  line `(ii) If in consequence of the requisition of the premises the person interested is compelled to`
  line `change his residence or place of business, the reasonable expenses (if any) incidental to such chance:`
  line
  line `Provided that where any person interested being aggrieved by the amount of compensation so`
  line `determined makes an application within the prescribed time to the Central Government for referring the`
  line `matter to an arbitrator, the amount of compensation to be paid shall be such as the arbitrator appointed in`
  line `this behalf by the Central Government may determine:`
  line
  line `Provided further that where there is any dispute as to the title to receive the compensation or as to the`
  line `apportionment of the amount of compensation, it shall be referred by the Central Government to an`
  line `arbitrator appointed in this behalf by that Government for determination, and shall be determined in`
  line `accordance with the decision of such arbitrator.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--In this sub-section, the expression person interested means the person who was in`
  line `actual possession of the premises requisitioned under section 7A immediately before the requisition, or`
  line `where no person was in such actual possession, the owner of such premises.`
  line
  line `(2) Whenever in pursuance of section 7A of the Central Government requisitions any vehicle, vessel,`
  line `or animal, there shall be paid to the owner thereof compensation the amount of which shall be determined`
  line `by the Central Government on the basis of the fares or rates prevailing in the locality for the hire of such`
  line `vehicle, vessel or animal:`
  line
  line `Provided that where the owner of such vehicle, vessel, or animal being aggrieved by the amount of`
  line `compensation so determined makes an application within the prescribed time to the Central Government`
  line `for referring the matter to an arbitrator, the amount of compensation to be paid shall be such as the`
  line `arbitrator appointed in this behalf by the Central Government may determine:`
  line
  line `Provided further that where immediately before the requisitioning the vehicle or vessel was by virtue`
  line `of a hire-purchase agreement in the possession of a person other than the owner, the amount determined`
  line `under this sub-section as the total compensation payable in respect of the requisition shall be apportioned`
  line `between that person and the owner in such manner as they may agree upon, and in default of agreement,`
  line `in such manner as an arbitrator appointed by the Central Government in this behalf may decide.]`
obj_root_law_sections_7_c:
  sectionId (6667)
  sectionNo 7C
  orderNo 12
  title `Power to obtain information.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_c_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 11 of 1994, s. 5 (w.e.f. 14-1-1994).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00002_194837_1517807319480&sectionId=6667&sectionno=7C&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00002_194837_1517807319480
obj_root_law_sections_7_c_content:
  string
  line `^1[7C. Power to obtain information.-- The Central Government may, with a view to requisitioning any`
  line `property under section 7A or determining the compensation payable under section 7B, by order, require`
  line `any person to furnish to such authority as may be specified in the order such information in his possession`
  line `relating to such property as may be so specified.]`
obj_root_law_sections_7_d:
  sectionId (6668)
  sectionNo 7D
  orderNo 13
  title `Power of entry into and inspection of premises, etc.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_d_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 11 of 1994, s. 5 (w.e.f. 14-1-1994).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00002_194837_1517807319480&sectionId=6668&sectionno=7D&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00002_194837_1517807319480
obj_root_law_sections_7_d_content:
  string
  line `^1[7D. Power of entry into and inspection of premises, etc.-- Any person authorised in this behalf by`
  line `the Central Government may enter into any premises and inspect such premises and any vehicle, vessel or animal therein for the purpose of determining whether, and if so in what manner, an order under`
  line `section 7A should be made in relation to such premises, vehicle, vessel or animal or with a view to`
  line `securing compliance with any order made under that section.]`
obj_root_law_sections_7_e:
  sectionId (6669)
  sectionNo 7E
  orderNo 14
  title `Eviction from requisitioned premises.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_e_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 11 of 1994, s. 5 (w.e.f. 14-1-1994).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00002_194837_1517807319480&sectionId=6669&sectionno=7E&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00002_194837_1517807319480
obj_root_law_sections_7_e_content:
  string
  line `^1[7E. Eviction from requisitioned premises.-- (1) Any person remaining in possession of any`
  line `requisitioned premises in contravention of any order made under section 7A may be summarily evicted`
  line `from the premises by any officer empowered by the Central Government in this behalf.`
  line
  line `(2) Any officer so empowered may, after giving to any woman not appearing in public reasonable`
  line `warning and facility to withdraw, remove or open any lock or bolt or break open any door of any building`
  line `or do any other act necessary for effecting such eviction.]`
obj_root_law_sections_7_f:
  sectionId (6670)
  sectionNo 7F
  orderNo 15
  title `Release of premises from requisition.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_f_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 11 of 1994, s. 5 (w.e.f. 14-1-1994).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00002_194837_1517807319480&sectionId=6670&sectionno=7F&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00002_194837_1517807319480
obj_root_law_sections_7_f_content:
  string
  line `^1[7F. Release of premises from requisition.-- (1) When any premises requisitioned under section 7A`
  line `are to be released from requisition, the possession thereof shall be delivered to the person from whom`
  line `possession thereof shall be delivered to the person from whom possession was taken at the time when the`
  line `premises were requisitioned, or if there were no such person, to the person deemed by the Central`
  line `Government to be the owner of such premises, and such delivery of possession shall be a full discharge of`
  line `the Central Government from all liabilities in respect of such delivery, but shall not prejudice any rights`
  line `in respect of the premises which any other person may be entitled by due process of law to enforce`
  line `against the person to whom possession of the premises is so delivered.`
  line
  line `(2) Where the person to whom possession of any premises requisitioned under section 7A is to be`
  line `given under sub-section (1) cannot be found or is not readily ascertainable or has no agent or any other`
  line `person empowered to accept delivery on his behalf, the Central Government shall cause a notice declaring`
  line `that such premises are released from requisition to be affixed on some conspicuous part of such premises`
  line `and publish the notice in the Official Gazette.`
  line
  line `(3) When a notice referred to in sub-section (2) is published in the Official Gazette, the premises`
  line `specified in such notice shall cease to be subject to requisition on and from the date of such publication`
  line `and be deemed to have been delivered to the person entitled to possession thereof, and the Central`
  line `Government shall not be liable for any compensation or other claim in respect of such premises for any`
  line `period after the said date.]`
obj_root_law_sections_7_g:
  sectionId (6671)
  sectionNo 7G
  orderNo 16
  title `Delegation of functions of the Central Government with regard to requisitioning.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_g_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 11 of 1994, s. 5 (w.e.f. 14-1-1994).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00002_194837_1517807319480&sectionId=6671&sectionno=7G&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00002_194837_1517807319480
obj_root_law_sections_7_g_content:
  string
  line `^1[7G. Delegation of functions of the Central Government with regard to requisitioning.-- The`
  line `Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette, direct that any powers conferred or any`
  line `duty imposed on that Government by any of the provisions of sections 7A to 7F shall, under such`
  line `conditions, if any, as may be specified in the direction, be exercised or discharged by such officer as may`
  line `be specified.]`
obj_root_law_sections_7_h:
  sectionId (6672)
  sectionNo 7H
  orderNo 17
  title `Penalty for contravention of any order regarding requisitioning.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_h_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 11 of 1994, s. 5 (w.e.f. 14-1-1994).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00002_194837_1517807319480&sectionId=6672&sectionno=7H&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00002_194837_1517807319480
obj_root_law_sections_7_h_content:
  string
  line `^1[7H. Penalty for contravention of any order regarding requisitioning.-- If any person contravenes`
  line `any order made under section 7A or section 7C, he shall be punishable with imprisonment for a term`
  line `which may extend to one year or with fine or with both.]`
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (6673)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 18
  title `Asking of questions and obligation to answer.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes `1 . Subs. by Act 11 of 1994, s. 6, for "State Government" (w.e.f. 14-1-1994).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00002_194837_1517807319480&sectionId=6673&sectionno=8&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00002_194837_1517807319480
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) A census officer may ask all such questions`
  line `of all persons within the limits of the local area for which he is appointed as, by instructions issued in this`
  line `behalf by the ^1`
  line `[Central Government] and published in the Official Gazette, he may be directed to ask.`
  line
  line `(2) Every person of whom any question is asked under sub-section (1) shall be legally bound to`
  line `answer such question to the best of his knowledge or belief:`
  line
  line `Provided that no person shall be bound to state the name of any female member of his household, and`
  line `no woman shall be bound to stale the name of her husband or deceased husband or of any other person`
  line `whose name she is forbidden by custom to mention.`
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (6674)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 19
  title `Occupier to permit access and affixing of numbers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00002_194837_1517807319480&sectionId=6674&sectionno=9&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00002_194837_1517807319480
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `Every person occupying any house,`
  line `enclosure, vessel or other place shall allow census-officers such access thereto as they may require for the`
  line `purposes of the census and as, having regard to the customs of the country, may be reasonable, and shall`
  line `allow them to paint on, or affix to, the place such letters, marks or numbers as may be necessary for the`
  line `purposes of the census.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (6675)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 20
  title `Occupier or manager to fill up schedule.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes `1 Subs. by Act 11 of 1994, s. 7, for "State Government".`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00002_194837_1517807319480&sectionId=6675&sectionno=10&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00002_194837_1517807319480
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `(1) Subject to such orders as the ^1`
  line [Census
  line `Commissioner] may issue in this behalf, a census-officer may, within the local area for which he is`
  line `appointed, leave or cause to be left a schedule at any dwelling-house or with the manager or any officer of`
  line `any commercial or industrial establishment, for the purpose of its being filled up by the occupiers of such`
  line `house or of any specified part thereof or by such manager or officer with such particulars as the ^1`
  line [Census
  line `Commissioner] may direct regarding the inmates of such house or part thereof, or the persons employed`
  line `under such manager or officer, as the case may be, at the time of the taking of the census.`
  line
  line `(2) When such schedule has been so left, the said occupier, manager or officer, as the case may be,`
  line `shall fill it up or cause it to be filled up to the best of' his knowledge or belief so far as regards the inmates`
  line `of such house or part thereof or the persons employed under him, as the case may be, at the time`
  line `aforesaid, and shall sign his name thereto and, when so required, shall deliver the schedule so filled up`
  line `and signed to the census-officer or to such person as the census-officer may direct.`
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (6676)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 21
  title Penalties.
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00002_194837_1517807319480&sectionId=6676&sectionno=11&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00002_194837_1517807319480
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) ^1`
  line `[(a) any census-officer or any person lawfully required to give assistance`
  line `towards the taking of census who refuses to perform any duty imposed upon him by this Act or any rule`
  line `made there under, or any person who hinders or obstructs another person in performing any such duty, or`
  line
  line `(aa) any census-officer or any person lawfully required to give assistance towards the taking of a`
  line `census who neglects to use reasonable diligence in performing any duty imposed upon him or in`
  line `obeying any order issued to him in accordance with this Act or any rule made there under, or any`
  line `person who hinders or obstructs another person in performing any such duty or obeying any such`
  line `order, or]`
  line
  line `(b) any census-officer who intentionally puts any offensive or improper question or knowingly`
  line `makes any false return or, without the previous sanction of the Central Government or the State`
  line `Government, discloses any information which he has received by means of, or for the purposes of, a`
  line `census return, or`
  line
  line `(c) any sorter, compiler or other member of the census staff who removes, secrets, damages or`
  line `destroys any census document or deals with any census document in a manner likely to falsify or`
  line `impair the tabulations of census results, or`
  line
  line ^2
  line `[(ca) any local authority which fails to comply with an order made under section 4A, or]`
  line
  line `(d) any person who intentionally gives a false answer to, or refuses to answer to the best of his`
  line `knowledge or belief, any question asked of him by a census-officer which he is legally bound by`
  line `section 8 to answer, or`
  line
  line `(e) any person occupying any house, enclosure, vessel or other place who refuses to allow a`
  line `census-officer such reasonable access thereto as he is required by section 9 to allow, or`
  line
  line `(f) any person who removes, obliterates, alters, or damages any letters, marks or numbers which`
  line `have been painted or affixed for the purposes of the census, or`
  line
  line `(g) any person who, having been required under section 10 to fill up a schedule, knowingly and`
  line `without sufficient cause to comply with the provisions of that section, or makes any false return there`
  line `under, or`
  line
  line `(h) any person who trespasses into a census office.`
  line `shall be punishable with fine which may extend to one thousand rupees and in case of a conviction under`
  line `part ^3`
  line `[(a), (b) or (c) shall also be punishable with imprisonment which may extend to three years.]`
  line
  line `(2) Whoever abets any offence under sub-section (1) shall be punishable with fine which may extend`
  line `to one thousand rupees.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line `1 Subs. by s. 8, ibid., for Part (a).`
  line
  line `2 Ins. by s. 8, ibid.`
  line
  line `3 Subs. by s. 8, ibid., for certain brackets, letters and words.`
  line
  line `4. The words "except the State of Jammu and Kashmir" omitted by Act 22 of 1959, s. 2 (w.e.f 19-5-1959)`
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (6677)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 22
  title `Sanction required for prosecutions.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes `1 Subs. by Act 11 of 1994, s. 9, for section 12.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00002_194837_1517807319480&sectionId=6677&sectionno=12&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00002_194837_1517807319480
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `^1 [12. Sanction required for prosecutions. Without prejudice to the provisions of section 197 of`
  line `the Code of Criminal Procedure, 1973 (2 of 1974), no prosecution under this Act shall be instituted except`
  line `with the previous sanction,`
  line
  line `(a) in the case of a person who is employed or was at the time of commission of the alleged`
  line `offence employed`
  line
  line `(i) in a company, as defined in section 3 of the Companies Act, 1956 (1 of 1956), in which`
  line `not less than fifty-one per cent. of the paid-up capital is held by the Central Government or any`
  line `company which is a subsidiary thereof within the meaning of that Act, or`
  line
  line `(ii) by a corporation or a local authority established by or under a Central Act which is owned`
  line `or controlled by the Central Government,`
  line `of the Central Government or of an authority authorised in this behalf by that Government; and`
  line
  line `(b) in the case of a person other than referred to in clause (a) of the State Government.]`
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (6678)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 23
  title `Operation of other laws not barred.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00002_194837_1517807319480&sectionId=6678&sectionno=13&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00002_194837_1517807319480
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `Nothing in this Act shall be deemed to prevent any`
  line `person from being prosecuted under any other law for any act or omission which constitutes an offence`
  line `under this Act:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such prosecution shall be instituted except with the previous sanction referred to in`
  line `section 12.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13_a:
  sectionId (6679)
  sectionNo 13A
  orderNo 24
  title `Certain offences to be cognizable and triable summarily.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_a_content
  footnotes `1 Ins. by s. 10, ibid.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00002_194837_1517807319480&sectionId=6679&sectionno=13A&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00002_194837_1517807319480
obj_root_law_sections_13_a_content:
  string
  line `^1 [13A. Certain offences to be cognizable and triable summarily.—(1) Notwithstanding anything`
  line `contained in the Code of Criminal Procedure. 1973 (2 of 1974), no police officer or court shall take`
  line `cognizance of any offence under part (a), (b) or (c) of sub-section (1) of section 11, except upon`
  line `information received from or on a complaint made by, as the case may be, the Director of Census`
  line `Operations or any officer authorised by him in this behalf.`
  line
  line `(2) Notwithstanding anything contained in the Code of Criminal Procedure 1973 (2 of 1974), every`
  line `offence punishable under part (a), (b) or (c) of sub-section (1) of section 11 may be tried summarily.]`
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (6680)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 25
  title Jurisdiction.
  content `No Court inferior to that of a ^1[Metropolitan Magistrate or a Judicial Magistrate of the first class] ^2***, shall try, whether under this Act or under any other law, any act or omission which constitutes an offence under this Act.`
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00002_194837_1517807319480&sectionId=6680&sectionno=14&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00002_194837_1517807319480
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line `1 Subs. by s. 11, ibid., for certain words.`
  line
  line `2. The words and letter "or in a Part B State, Magistrate corresponding to magistrate of second class" omitted by Adaptation of`
  line `Laws (No. 3) Order, 1956`
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (6681)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 26
  title `Records of census not open to inspection of admissible in evidence.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00002_194837_1517807319480&sectionId=6681&sectionno=15&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00002_194837_1517807319480
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `No person shall have a`
  line `right to inspect any book, register or record made by a census-officer in the discharge of his duty as such,`
  line `or any schedule delivered under section 10 and notwithstanding anything to the contrary in the Indian`
  line `Evidence Act, 1872 (1 of 1872), no entry in any such book, register, record or schedule shall be`
  line `admissible as evidence in any civil proceeding whatsoever or in any criminal proceeding other than a`
  line `prosecution under this Act or any other law for any act or omission which constitutes an offence under`
  line `this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15_a:
  sectionId (6682)
  sectionNo 15A
  orderNo 27
  title `Protection of service interests of members of census staff.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_a_content
  footnotes `1 . Ins. by Act 11 of 1994, s. 12.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00002_194837_1517807319480&sectionId=6682&sectionno=15A&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00002_194837_1517807319480
obj_root_law_sections_15_a_content:
  string
  line `^1 [15A. Protection of service interests of members of census staff.No member of the census staff`
  line `shall suffer any disability in service by reason of his being on census duty and the period spent by him on`
  line `such census duty shall be deemed to be the duty under his lending employer and any duty performed`
  line `under this Act shall not in any manner affect the right of promotion or other advancement in his original`
  line service.]
obj_root_law_sections_15_b:
  sectionId (6683)
  sectionNo 15B
  orderNo 28
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_b_content
  footnotes `1. Ins. by Act 11 of 1994, s. 12.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00002_194837_1517807319480&sectionId=6683&sectionno=15B&orderno=28&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00002_194837_1517807319480
obj_root_law_sections_15_b_content:
  string
  line `^1[15B. Protection of action taken in good faith.-- No suit, prosecution or other legal proceeding shall`
  line `lie against the Census Commissioner or any Director of Census Operations or any census-officer or any`
  line `member of the census staff for anything which is in good faith done or intended to be done under this Act`
  line `or the rules made thereunder.]`
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (6684)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 29
  title `Temporary suspension of other laws as to mode of taking census in municipalities.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes `1 Subs. by Act 56 of 1974, s. 3 and the Second Schedule, for "Superintendent of Census Operations" (w.e.f. 20-12-1974).`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00002_194837_1517807319480&sectionId=6684&sectionno=16&orderno=29&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00002_194837_1517807319480
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything in any enactment or rule with respect to the mode in which a`
  line `census is to be taken in any municipality, the municipal authority, in consultation with the ^1`
  line `[Director of`
  line `Census Operation] or with such other authority as the State Government may authorise in this behalf,`
  line `shall, at the time appointed for the taking of any census cause the census of the municipality to be taken`
  line `wholly or in part by any method authorised by or under this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (6685)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 30
  title `Grant of statistical abstracts.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00002_194837_1517807319480&sectionId=6685&sectionno=17&orderno=30&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00002_194837_1517807319480
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[Subject to the provisions of section 15, the Census`
  line `Commissioner or any Director of Census Operations] may, If he so thinks fit, at the request and cost`
  line `(to be determined by him) of any local authority or person, cause abstracts to be prepared and supplied`
  line `containing any such statistical information as can be derived from the census returns for ^2`
  line `[lndia or any`
  line `State], as the case may be, being information which is not contained in any published report and which in`
  line `his opinion it is reasonable for that authority or person to require.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line `1 Subs. by Act 11 of 1994, s. 13, for certain words.`
  line
  line `2 Subs by the A. O. 1950, for "the provinces of India or the Province"`
obj_root_law_sections_17_a:
  sectionId (6686)
  sectionNo 17A
  orderNo 31
  title `Power to extend the provisions of Act to other operations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_a_content
  footnotes `1 . Ins. by Act 11 of 1994, s. 14.`
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00002_194837_1517807319480&sectionId=6686&sectionno=17A&orderno=31&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00002_194837_1517807319480
obj_root_law_sections_17_a_content:
  string
  line `^1 [17A. Power to extend the provisions of Act to other operations.—`
  line `The Central Government may,`
  line `by notification in the Official Gazette, extend the provisions of this Act, with such restrictions and`
  line `modifications as it thinks fit, to pre-tests, pilot studies, census of houses which precede the population`
  line `count and post enumeration check and evaluation studies or statistical surveys or any other operation as`
  line `may be deemed necessary for the purpose of census.]`
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (6687)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 32
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_5_40_00002_194837_1517807319480&sectionId=6687&sectionno=18&orderno=32&orgactid=AC_CEN_5_40_00002_194837_1517807319480
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may ^1`
  line `[by notification in the Official`
  line `Gazette] Act may make rules for carrying out the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, the Central`
  line `Government may make rules providing for the appointment of census-officers and of persons to the form`
  line `any of the duties of census-officers or to give assistance towards the taking of a census, and for the`
  line `general instructions to be issued to such officers and persons ^2`
  line `[and providing for the manner of service of`
  line `of orders regarding requisitioning of premises, or vehicle; vessel or animal and the time within which the`
  line `application may be made to it by any interested person aggrieved by the amount of compensation`
  line `determined under section 7B for referring the matter to an arbitrator.]`
  line
  line ^3
  line `[(3) Every rule made under this section shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before each`
  line `House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised in`
  line `one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately`
  line `following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification`
  line `in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall thereafter have effect only`
  line `in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such modification or`
  line `annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under that rule.]`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line `1 Ins. by Act 4 of 1986, s. 2 and the Schedule (w.e.f. 15-5-1986).`
  line
  line `2 Added by Act 11 of 1994, s. 15.`
  line
  line `3 Ins. by Act 4 of 1986, s. 2 and the Schedule (w.e.f. 15-5-1986).`
